Brick_Command.doc: A Command is an output point that directly determines the behavior of equipment and/or affects relevant operational points.

Brick_Sensor.doc: A Sensor is an input point that represents the value of a device or instrument designed to detect and measure a variable (ASHRAE Dictionary).

Brick_Alarm.doc: Alarm points are signals (either audible or visual) that alert an operator to an off-normal condition which requires some form of corrective action

Brick_Status.doc: A Status is input point that reports the current operating mode, state, position, or condition of an item. Statuses are observations and should be considered 'read-only'

Brick_Setpoint.doc: A Setpoint is an input value at which the desired property is set
